"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147987","Department for Transport","false","2019-10-08","<p>Transport for the North, the Department for Transport and the rail industry monitor timetable changes and agreed actions for the December 2018 timetable which gave passengers a more resilient service on the Huddersfield line. These measures have continued into 2019 and the planned introduction of new longer trains and timetable improvements for this December means further stability, faster services and increased capacity.</p>","Daventry","Chris Heaton-Harris",,"2019-10-08T09:53:57.01Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147987/answer","Biography information for Chris Heaton-Harris","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147987/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147987/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-10-02","Railways: Huddersfield","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the adequacy of the latest timetable and scope of improvements being planned to TransPennine Services on the Huddersfield Rail line; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Reynolds","Stalybridge and Hyde","Jonathan Reynolds","293566"
