"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147440","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-10-07","<p>This is a matter for Ofcom as the UK’s independent competition regulator for telecoms. However, in general, the UK has a competitive Internet Service Provider (ISP) market as a result of the work that Ofcom has done to promote competition at the retail level by providing regulated access to BT Openreach’s national broadband network.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The Government is also working with Ofcom to promote greater competition at a network level, as this is one of the key ways to meet our ambition for nationwide coverage of faster and more resilient gigabit broadband networks as soon as possible.</p><p> </p>","Boston and Skegness","Matt Warman",,"2019-10-07T12:55:07.937Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147440/answer","Biography information for Matt Warman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147440/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147440/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-10-01","Internet Service Providers: Monopolies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what recent steps her Department is taking to tackle Internet Service Provider monopolies.","false","Biography information for Jack Lopresti","Filton and Bradley Stoke","Jack Lopresti","292888"
