"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147519","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-10-07","<p>The Supplementary Estimates 2018-19 relate to the activities described for 2018-19 budget, while the Main Estimates 2019-20 reflect the activities for the 2019-20 budget.</p>","Berwick-upon-Tweed","Anne-Marie Trevelyan","292880 ; 292881","2019-10-07T16:18:49.37Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147519/answer","Biography information for Anne-Marie Trevelyan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147519/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147519/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-10-01","Defence: Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, for what reasons RDEL in the Supplementary Estimates 2018-19 and the Main Estimates for 2019-20 are different for (a) infrastructure costs, (b) equipment support costs, (c) other costs and services and (d) administration costs.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","292879"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147520","Treasury","false","2019-10-08","<p>The Government carefully considered the case for reform prior to announcing this change last year, and it is the Government’s view that taxpayers can reasonably expect that when they have successfully paid their taxes, these go to fund public services as intended.</p><p> </p><p>This measure represents a proportionate approach that balances the interests of taxpayers, the Exchequer, and other creditors.</p><p> </p><p>The Government expects the impact on the sustainability of Pension Protection Fund (PPF) to be marginal. This reform will not lead to a significant change in recoveries to the PPF compared to current returns.</p><p> </p><p>The Government does not expect this reform to affect significantly SMEs’ access to finance or corporate insolvencies, and in line with the Government’s commitment to open and consultative policymaking is engaging with a wide variety of stakeholders to ensure policy changes are well informed and based upon the best available evidence.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","292833 ; 292834 ; 292835","2019-10-08T07:42:11.34Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147520/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147520/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147520/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-10-01","Insolvency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, what discussions his officials had with the Insolvency Service on the draft Finance Bill 2019-20 prior to its publication on 11 July 2019; and whether views were sought on the policy to make HMRC a secondary preferential creditor in insolvencies.","false","Biography information for Mr Adrian Bailey","West Bromwich West","Mr Adrian Bailey","292832"
