"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1146922","Department for Transport","false","2019-10-08","<p>The Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency (DVSA) has not reduced the number of staff conducting roadside mechanical spot checks on lorries between 2016 and 2019.</p><p> </p><p>The DVSA targets serious and serially non-compliant operators and drivers to protect British road users from unsafe drivers and vehicles.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Vere of Norbiton",,"2019-10-08T11:31:25.073Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1146922/answer","Biography information for Baroness Vere of Norbiton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1146922/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1146922/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-09-30","Large Goods Vehicles: Inspections","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government, further to the Written Answer by Baroness Vere of Norbiton on 9 September (HL17707), whether the number of staff of the Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency conducting roadside mechanical spot checks on lorries was reduced between 2016 and 2019.","false","Biography information for Lord Bradshaw",,"Lord Bradshaw","HL17896"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1146923","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-10-08","<p>I can confirm that the 2019-20 local government finance settlement was higher than the 2018-19 settlement. Core Spending Power increased from £45.1 billion in 2018-19 to £46.2 billion in 2019-20, a cash-increase of 2.5% and a real-terms increase in resources available to local authorities.</p>",,"Viscount Younger of Leckie",,"2019-10-08T14:41:42.017Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1146923/answer","Biography information for Viscount Younger of Leckie","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1146923/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1146923/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-09-30","Local Government Finance","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government, further to the Written Answer by Baroness Vere of Norbiton on 9 September (HL17590), whether the 2019–20 local government finance settlement was higher than the 2018–19 settlement.","false","Biography information for Lord Bradshaw",,"Lord Bradshaw","HL17897"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1146924","Department for Transport","false","2019-10-08","<p>Highways England is committed to mitigating noise pollution on the Strategic Road Network. Highways England’s key performance indicator for noise requires mitigation to be installed at 1,150 Noise Important Areas by the end of the first Road Investment Strategy period in March 2020. To support this objective Highways England is:</p><p> </p><ul><li>installing low noise surfacing, where appropriate, as part of the road renewal programme, for example outside houses, schools and hospitals;</li><li>when delivering schemes, seeking to mitigate potential noise impacts in line with national policy, through the use of: low noise surfacing, noise barriers, earth bunds, and through the scheme design process;</li><li>delivering new noise barriers through the Environmental Designated Fund, and renewal of existing noise barriers where required; and</li><li>installing acoustic glazing to residential properties in Noise Important Areas, delivered through the Environmental Designated Fund.</li></ul><p> </p><p>Further to the work of HE, the Department for Transport is promoting the use of Electric Vehicles which will significantly reduce the noise pollution on major roads.</p>",,"Baroness Vere of Norbiton",,"2019-10-08T11:31:57.113Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1146924/answer","Biography information for Baroness Vere of Norbiton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1146924/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1146924/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-09-30","Road Traffic: Noise","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what plans they have, if any, to undertake work to reduce road traffic noise along major roads.","false","Biography information for Lord Bradshaw",,"Lord Bradshaw","HL17898"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1146925","Department for Transport","false","2019-10-08","<p>Miles per Technical Incident is the common performance statistic calculated for all classes of trains used for passenger services on the national network. These statistics are collated by the Rail Delivery Group from data collated from the train operators. The Hitachi Intercity Express Trains owned by Agility Trains West are included in these statistics.</p>",,"Baroness Vere of Norbiton",,"2019-10-08T11:18:06.437Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1146925/answer","Biography information for Baroness Vere of Norbiton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1146925/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1146925/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-09-30","Agility Trains: Standards","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether Agility Trains West account for delays incurred by their trains using the miles per casualty measure.","false","Biography information for Lord Bradshaw",,"Lord Bradshaw","HL17899"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1146926","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2019-10-08","<p><em>It has not proved possible to respond to this question in the time available before Prorogation. Ministers will correspond directly with the Member.</em></p>",,"Lord Gardiner of Kimble",,"2019-10-08T16:13:57.217Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1146926/answer","Biography information for Lord Gardiner of Kimble","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1146926/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1146926/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2019-09-30","Bridleways and Public Footpaths: Lake District National Park","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what assessment they have made of the damage caused to footpaths and bridleways in the Lake District National Park; and what measures are available to park authorities to remedy such damage.","false","Biography information for Lord Bradshaw",,"Lord Bradshaw","HL17900"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1146927","Department for Transport","false","2019-10-08","<p>The franchise agreement sets out operational performance benchmarks for Cancellations, Delay Minutes and Short Formations. Network Rail monitors and measures the operational performance of the railways and the Train Operator will provide these numbers to the Department for Transport to monitor their performance against the benchmarks.</p><p>The East Midlands Railway franchise agreement, which contains the franchise specific benchmarks, will be published on the gov.uk website in due course.</p>",,"Baroness Vere of Norbiton",,"2019-10-08T11:15:30.273Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1146927/answer","Biography information for Baroness Vere of Norbiton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1146927/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1146927/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-09-30","East Midlands Railway: Standards","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what are the contractual requirements between East Midlands Railway and the Department for Transport for the operational performance of that line; and who is responsible for measuring that performance.","false","Biography information for Lord Bradshaw",,"Lord Bradshaw","HL17901"
